The paper discusses deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). It focuses on evaluating the generalization capabilities of deep reinforcement learning agents, which involves analyzing their behavior in different states and situations (cs.RO, cs.SY). The authors also use a benchmark task that involves visual inputs, suggesting a potential connection to computer vision (cs.CV).
